President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Dr. Michael W. Hail for a key Administration post as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Harry S Truman Scholarship Foundation. Dr. Hail is currently a Professor of Government at Morehead State University, where he has been since 2007. He also serves as the Assistant Dean of the School of Public Affairs at Morehead State University. In addition, Dr. Hail is the Associate Director of the Institute for Federalism and Intergovernmental Relations at the University of Kentucky. He has held various teaching positions at different universities, including the University of Delaware and the University of Kentucky. Dr. Hail has an A.B. from Centre College of Kentucky, an M.A. from Eastern Kentucky University, and a Ph.D. from the University of Delaware.